MinionsWeb.com Web Blaster Cobweb Shooters - Webs so real, we fool spiders!

No other web guns are made like MinionsWeb products.
For 10 years Minions Web has been hand fabricating 5 models of cob web guns in the USA. 

All 5 model cobweb shooters are designed and built as tools, not toys.  They are rugged and built to last for years of service for the home haunter, haunted houses, theater design, photography studios, movie sets both indoors and outdoors, for the amateur & professional alike.  

Dressing a scene is the most important part of and most often forgotten element in any haunt.  With a MinionsWeb Cobweb Blaster, any haunter can add cobwebs to an ordinary scene and bring it to life. Detail or cover your display with realistic looking cobwebs quickly and effectively.

View all the MinionsWeb web guns at http://www.minionsweb.com/osStore/cob-webs-web-shooters-c-1_17_22.html

All Minions Web Hot Glue Cob Webbers run 1/4" airline internally to provide superior air flow and volume at substantially lower pressure.  There are poor imitations out there using 1/8" - 3/16" airline. 

Only Minions Web gun tips venturi draw webbing material into the integrated compressed air stream, resulting in less waste (gobbing), the finest appearance and precise application of webbing materials.  MinionsWeb.com webbing is pulled from the gun, not pushed, creating the finest gossamer like web strands possible.

Our models allow you the ability to apply webbing within inches of your scenery or blow webs up to an incredible 50 feet away!
You control the direction, amount and density of webs easily with the integrated valve and trigger.  Our patented design allows you to create more webs, at less pressure, consuming less hot glue, than any other web gun in the world.

Our all metal, 450 PSI rated, integrated controls and airway components are safely contained within the webber unlike others on the market, protecting the airway from damage due to mishandling.

Have a REAL haunt?  Larger than a few areas that you want to dress out with webbing for that ever-so-creepy effect?  You NEED a MinionsWeb webber !!! 

Other web shooters require you to push the glue thru with your thumb! Or they use glue that will only work in their toy like disposable gun.  Not the guns and glues from from MinionsWeb!  Our webbers are ergonomically designed with squeeze style triggers for ease of use.

Minions Web is the only manufacturer of USA made fire safe and food safe web sticks in over 15 colors, black light and glow in the dark versions, with more on the way.  Minions Web WebStix  will work in ANY 1/2" hot glue gun or cobweb spinner.

description:
Clark University vs Wheaton College - Cougar sophomore Will Van Noppen provided instant fireworks when he scored his fourth goal of the season off of the opening touch, launching a shot from the center circle that sailed over the head of Wheaton goalkeeper. The goal which came just four seconds into the match ties the NCAA record for the fastest goal ever to start a match in Division III men's soccer history.

Final score Clark 1 - Wheaton

For all the non-beleivers.

From the FIFA Laws of the Game at the FIFA website.
Kick-off
A kick-off is a way of starting or restarting play
 - at the start of the match
 - after a goal has been scored
 - at the start of the second half of the match
 - at the start of each period of extra time, where applicable

A goal may be scored directly from the kick-off.

Procedure
 - all players must be in their own half of the field of play
 - the opponents of the team taking the kick-off are at least 9.15 m
(10 yds) from the ball until it is in play
 - the ball must be stationary on the centre mark
 - the referee gives a signal
 - the ball is in play when it is kicked and moves forward
 - the kicker must not touch the ball again until it has touched another player

After a team scores a goal, the kick-off is taken by the other team.

This goal is a legal goal!

6 by Six is a collection of card magic from Michael Six Muldoon. Included on this dvd are six effects you can do with ANY deck of cards, PLUS two bonus routines and a incredibly simple yet deceptive move to switch a card that has not been released any where, ever! It is finally shared here in a special section with over 35 - minutes of in depth detail, recorded in full HD. This is real world magic, that you will perform! Ranging from renditions on classics to incredible SELF-WORKING routines, this dvd is a must for anyone who loves card magic. 

New Found Blood: A multi-phase sandwich and coincidence routine with a killer ending and even includes 3 variations! 

Two Ton Triumph: An in the hands triumph with a super clean get ready, to eliminate any "fishy moves". Perfect for the walk around performer or anyone looking for an anytime, anywhere version of Michael's Modern Triumph. 

No Stopping Me: A self working routine done under impossible conditions. You can have a card looked at in the deck, have the spectator deal through and stop them at their card! The perfect stop trick, with a great psychological through off. 

Invisible Flush: Larry Jennings Invisible Palm routine with an impossible ending! You can cause all the Aces to transform into a Royal Flush, a logical ending to one of the best routines ever created.

description:
Het merk Kuoni verdwijnt het komende jaar van de Nederlandse markt en gaat verder als Tenzing Travel, dat heeft Hans de Wilde (directeur Kuoni) bekend gemaakt in een exclusief interview met TravelPro. “Voor ons is dit de volgende stap in de ontwikkeling van het bedrijf. Het gaat hier heel erg goed en daarom hebben we met het oog op de toekomst gekozen voor een nieuwe merknaam”, aldus De Wilde. 

‘‘Voor de rebranding gaan we de tijd nemen. De licentie voor het merk ‘Kuoni’ eindigt pas volgend jaar. Vanaf eind augustus gaan we in de loop van een jaar langzaamaan rebranden van Kuoni naar Tenzing Travel. Het eerste half jaar zullen we gaan werken met een transitie-logo waarop staat ‘Kuoni wordt Tenzing Travel’ dat we overal zullen gebruiken. De eerste maanden richten we ons vooral op alles intern en op de reisbureaus en vanaf december gaan we ons ook op de B2C richten. Vanaf het moment dat de gidsen voor het seizoen 2015-2016 uitkomen zal de naam Kuoni helemaal zijn verdwenen.’’

“De naam ‘Tenzing’ komt van Tenzing Norgay, de Nepalese gids en sherpa van Edmund Hillary, de Nieuw-Zeelander die als de top van de Mount Everest bereikte in 1953. Wij vinden het belangrijk dat er een mooi verhaal achter de merknaam zit. Zonder Tenzing had Hillary nooit de top bereikt, want Tenzing heeft de reis voorbereid, kende de route en heeft Hillary geholpen om problemen te overwinnen. Wij hebben ons daardoor laten inspireren en gezegd: wij willen de Tenzing, de gids zijn voor onze klanten.”.

‘‘Met dit nieuwe merk kunnen we naar de toekomst toe veel meer. Wij willen de meest toonaangevende reisorganisatie zijn op het gebied van verre reizen. Dat betekent niet dat wij de grootste willen zijn. Ik heb het over kennis, innovatie, kwaliteit en klanttevredenheid. Als je kijkt naar de offerte tool die we hebben, de reisdocumenten, wat we doen op het gebied van kennis- en conceptontwikkeling zijn we goed bezig. Wanneer mensen vragen naar een goede reisorganisatie voor verre reizen dan moet Tenzing Travel worden genoemd. Ik wil een goede, kwalitatieve verre reizen organisatie zijn die stabiel, winstgevend en toonaangevend is en ook gericht is op continuïteit...en waar zowel de medewerkers, de reisbureaus als de klanten elk op hun eigen manier toch wel een beetje trots op zijn’’, aldus De Wilde. 

De Wilde is niet van plan iets aan de strategie te veranderen, maar laat weten versneld verder te  gaan met een aantal pijlers binnen de strategie. De Wilde: “Wij werden nog teveel gezien als een generalist, terwijl wij concurreren met specialisten. Met Tenzing Travel willen we meer specialisme uitstralen per bestemming en daarom krijgt iedere bestemming ook een eigen label (Tenzing Travel America, Tenzing Travel Africa, Tenzing Travel Asia, Tenzing Travel Down Under, Tenzing Travel Caribbean en Tenzing Travel Latin America) met een eigen kleur, een eigen Business Unit waar alle kennis zit en een eigen website (met een eigen kleurstelling en eigen look & feel). Daarmee kunnen we heel sterk op bestemmingsniveau een bepaalde positionering innemen. We gaan de bestemmingen en daarmee ook de brochures meer splitsen, zo krijgt Azië bijvoorbeeld twee brochures”. Het volledige interview met Hans de Wilde is te lezen in TravelPro 17 die donderdag 21 augustus verschijnt.
title: Kuoni verder als Tenzing Travel

Welcome, newcomer. To the place of bones. 

The last thing you remember is receiving an unsatisfying answer. A plunge through the fundamental chaos takes you to a place of bones. Great power can be found within the Ossuary, but those who are not lying to themselves are lying to you. Ossuary is a dark, puzzling game where the player explores a strange underworld full of people slowly gathering dust. It explores themes of order, chaos, sin, and virtue, and it draws strong inspiration from the Discordian religious tradition.

Transcript:

Greetings, newcomer. It's been some time since we've had a new warm body here. Since you are useless, please wait until you are told what to do and how to think.

You are fortunate enough to arrive in the Ossuary. We were brought to this haven by our departed leader, Greyface. Since he left, we have dedicated ourselves to virtue: Order, Justice, Temperance, Fortitude, and Prudence.

Be warned: while we are working to make this place into a paradise, sin still exists here. Do not allow yourself to be corrupted by it. Keep yourself pure and ordered and you will fit in perfectly.

For more information, speak with our leaders, the Sacred Order of the Defamation League.

Welcome, newcomer. To the place of bones.
title: Ossuary Welcome Trailer

The latest episode of our Designers' Worlds series stars London streetwear prince Nasir Mazhar, who invited Chris Read and i-D out for the sexiest of spring/summer 15 after parties. In a season that tightened and heightened the brand's head-to-toe uniform, Nasir collaborated with Skepta for a bespoke soundtrack that boomed as his designs two-stepped beyond the catwalk and straight into its spiritual home, the club. Riding the grime great's flow as part of the Red Bull Catwalk Studio, Nasir's daydream of hyper reality bendy diva dived down the poles of Metropolis for a night that London Collections: Men had never seen. Capturing everything, we lurked in shadows and danced in the spotlight while the seedy East London institution blossomed into the designer's vision of paradise. http://www.b2review.com/dutch-iris-holland-grown-bulbs-in-april-bloom/ Dutch iris is one of around 260 iris varieties and these are said to be made from "Holland grown bulbs."  This video was taken on April 2, 2011 when the dutch iris is in bloom as an early spring flower.  I had planted these free bulbs that I received without request in the rest of my order from directgardening.com around 5 months ago when they were planted in this 18 gallon container with amended compost.  Really, the best way to start is to find a few fresh bulbs from a friend and save the online order for something more difficult to find.
Dutch Iris In Bloom

In about a month after the bulbs had been placed in the soil, a few sword-like shoots appeared.  These shoots grew to over a foot tall and then the flower shoots started, became thick, and then flowered over the last five months.  The cut flowers last well in arrangements and should continue to provide new blooms each year from the rhizomes.


Dutch Iris Holland Grown In Bloom
This has been a very easy flower to grow so I would suggest it for the novice gardener.  The bloom is worth the effort which is very little.  Just keep the soil moist, keep the bulbs a little over an inch deep in the rich soil for a few months, and watch the flowers explode!
title: Dutch Iris Holland Grown Bulbs In April Bloom

description:
http://www.plumberx.com
These " How to" Plumbing videos are a must. Even if you feel you know everything there is to know about plumbing repairs, there is something in these videos for you. Just imagine if you could watch a plumber install and repair plumbing day by day, hour after hour. Could you imagine what you would learn? Yes, you could learn enough to start your own plumbing repair service. Not only would you save money, but you can make money. Well, your wish has come true. On these videos you will find and learn all the tricks of the trade that the pros already know. No more biting your nails when you call the plumber. No more taking off from work, staying at home waiting for the plumber to show up only to have him / her call you to say he or she may have to reschedule. With these plumbing videos you will be impressed and happy to know the knowledge is just an arm's reach away. 
Pick up any one of the videos; toilet, bath, sink, tub and shower, kitchen sink, hot water heater and the sump pump. The list goes on. Every video has been created by a licensed plumber with over 25 years experience in plumbing repairs services. You will be watching a real plumber doing service, not someone that can just talk the talk, but can walk the walk. 
There are no plumbing videos out there like these. It took years to develop these videos. We know there is a need out there for these plumbing repair videos. After years of plumbing service, we have come across many people who could really not afford a plumber and went years without plumbing services, even to the point that they would have to move from their home or pay thousands of dollars for plumbing repairs. If only these people had this knowledge, they could and would have saved their home and their money. 
We know you are out there. We have come to save the day. Everyone does not have $90 to $200 to have a plumber come out just to tell them what the problem is and what it will cost to fix. We are not trying to put plumbers out of work. We are just trying to keep you out of the red. There will still be times when you may need a plumber, but wouldn't you feel good understanding what the plumber is doing and what you are getting for your money. You know that you are not going to be cheated because you have a better understanding of the problem and how it can be fixed.

Vorbildlich geführt, werden in der aufstrebenden, modernen Autowerkstatt sämtliche Aufgaben rund um Autos aller Marken und jeder Bauart durchgeführt. Neben der gründlichen Ausbildung sind es die Wertschätzung und das Vertrauen der Firmenführung jedem einzelnen Mitarbeiter gegenüber, die stets hervorragende Arbeiten sicherstellen.

description:
A delicious Indian recipe of cabbage & potato!

Ingredients-200 gm cabbage 
250 gm potatoes 
1/2 tsp asafetida 
1 tsp turmeric powder 
1 tsp cumin seeds 
2 tsp coriander powder 
1 green chilli chopped 
2 tbsp oil 
5-6 curry leaves  
Salt to taste

Preparation-Heat the oil,to it add asafetida,cumin seeds and curry leaves Mix well. Next add the dry spices, turmeric powder,coriander powder and finely chopped chilli. Mix well.Now add the potatoes and cabbage and toss well. Add salt and let it cook on slow flame . Garnish with coriander leaves and serve hot with rotis
title: Aloo Patta Gobi Recipe - {potato & cabbage}

description:
Spicy Pulao with stir fry Brinjals is an amazing rice dish preparation commonly known as Vangi masala bhath made with eggplant/ brinjal added to basmati rice with aromatic masala playing the key role 

Egg plant          500g
Poppy seeds     2 tb
Red chilly        4 n
Pepper corn     6 n
Sesame seeds   2 tb
Dry coconut     8 small   pieces
Coriander seeds        1 tb
Ghee                 3 tb
Mustard seeds  ½ ts
Cumin seeds    ½ ts
Cashew nuts    6 n
Green chilly     5 n
Salt
Turmeric pinch
Boiled Rice               1 c
Whole garam masala (all)  1 n
 
 
 
1.        Take a pan add whole garam masala, poppy seeds, red chilly, pepper corn, sesame seeds, dry coconut, coriander seeds, dry roast in a slow flame, and make a powder.
2.        Heat ghee in a pan and mustard seeds, cumin seeds, and add cashew nuts, green chilly, egg plant, salt, add pinch of turmeric, add masala, mix it, and add boiled rice and toss this and switch off the flame.

description:
http://www.XeroShoes.com -- If you're making barefoot running shoes (also called Tarahumara huaraches running sandals), you'll have to thread the lace through the ankle and toe holes in the soles.

For some laces, this can be a bit tricky.

In this video I'll show you a few tips for lacing your Xero Shoes barefoot sandals.

In short, you can melt the end of the lace and feed it through the holes in the minimalist outsole, or you can use a hair pin to help get the cord through the outsole.

If you haven't tried running barefoot or in a pair of minimalist sandals or running shoes, you must! Feel The Freedom of natural movement!
title: Barefoot Running Sandal Lacing Tip - Huaraches Barefoot Shoes - Xero Shoes

description:
★★★★ Hola y bienvenido a este video, en esta ocasión compartiré contigo los ►sintomas de colitis◄

Entre los principales sintomas tenemos:
-Cólicos Abdominales
-Diarrea
-Vómitos

Otros sintomas no muy comunes pero que también se deben tomar en cuenta son:
-Estomago inflamado por la retención de gases
-Ruido y dolor abdominal

Dependiendo del grado de colitis se pueden presentar sintomas mas severos como ser:
-Sangrado
-Dolor abdominal
-Nauseas
-Vómitos mas frecuentes
-Diarrea intensa

La colitis es una enfermedad inflamatoria del colon (el intestino grueso) y del recto. Está caracterizada por la inflamación y ulceración de la pared interior del colon. 
El diagnóstico definitivo lo establece la endoscopia, los gastroenterólogos son los especialistas que suelen diagnosticar y tratar esta enfermedad.

Existen diversas teorías sobre las causas de la colitis ulcerosa, ninguna de ellas comprobada. No se conoce la causa de la colitis ulcerosa, y actualmente no hay cura, excepto a través de la extirpación quirúrgica del colon. Se cree que puede ser un virus o una bacteria que interactúa con el sistema inmune del cuerpo y desencadena una reacción inflamatoria en la pared intestinal.

Espero que esta información sobre "sintomas de colitis" te sea muy útil, no olvides darle me gusta a este video y compartirlo con tus amigos, también puedes suscribirte en mi canal para que cada vez que suba un nuevo video seas el primero en ser informado. Un abrazo y nos vemos en el siguiente video
title: Sintomas De Colitis

Stampa rara del cardellino di Audubon del doppio dell'elefante dell'edizione americana di Lipsia American Goldfinch Audubon Double Elephant Leipzig Edition Rare Print This is a rare double elephant sized print from the Audubon Leipzig limited edition numbered 676/1000. Size of each print overall is 38.5 x 25.5 inches (980 x 650 mm) and the size of this print without margins is // X // (// x //). The Leipzig Edition is printed on heavy cardstock like paper, without a gloss. The prints are collotypes. A collotype is an outdated printing technique that was commercially developed around 1868, and all but abandoned after Wold War 2. The collotype was the most accurate and beautiful photomechanical printing method of its time. Its process begins by drying a layer of light sensitive chrome gelatine on a glass plate (similar to the emulsions used by photographic glass plates). This gelatine coated glass plate becomes the printing. Like chromolithography, collotype is a multi-plate printing process.

description:
Video courtesy: http://www.youtube.com/farhadswiss

The captain of an Iran Air Boeing 727 has managed to land his aircraft at Tehran's Mehrabad airport even though its nose landing gear failed to unfold. Captain Hooshang Shahbazi's piloting skill saved the lives of some 94 passengers and 19 crew members. Footage of the miraculous landing on October 18 became an internet sensation and Shahbazi's Facebook page ( http://www.facebook.com/shahbazi200 ) has attracted hundreds of new friends.

The flight IR-742 from Moscow, Sheremetyevo was on approach to Tehran's Imam Khomeini Airport around when the crew did not receive a down and locked indication for the nose gear and aborted the approach. Following unsuccessful troubleshooting the crew decided to divert to Tehran's Mehrabad Airport where a low approach confirmed the nose gear was not extended. The crew subsequently performed a landing without the nose gear and came to a stand still on both main gear and the nose of the aircraft. The aircraft was evacuated, no injuries occurred.

RT on Twitter http://twitter.com/RT_com 
RT on Facebook http://www.facebook.com/RTnews
title: 'Miracle' landing without nose gear: Iran Air ace saves lives on Boeing 727

Dopo anni di studio, ricerche e sperimentazioni nel vasto e complesso campo del cosiddetto "Linguaggio Rovesciato", Riccardo Misto  ha sviluppato un organico sistema teorico-pratico che permette un'accurata indagine e analisi dei messaggi inconsci che la mente costantemente invia, parallelamente al normale discorso palese, sotto forma di frasi chiaramente rintracciabili nel flusso verbale ascoltato a rovescia.
Grazie a funzionali programmi informatici che la moderna tecnologia digitale mette oggi a disposizione, e con una speciale tecnica di analisi approfondita, è possibile isolare, decodificare e interpretare questo metalinguaggio in chiave terapeutica, al fine di scoprire in breve tempo preziose informazioni di cui la mente è a conoscenza a livello subconscio: grazie a queste si possono quindi risolvere problematiche personali e familiari a carattere psicosomatico, andando così a modificare il comportamento indesiderato e sradicando alla radice abitudini fisse che limitano la completa potenzialità ed efficienza della persona.
In poche sedute è possibile scoprire i blocchi subconsci e con un programma di destrutturazione e riprogrammazione mentale, ottenere la scomparsa di una vasta gamma di problematiche psicologiche, comportamentali, fisiche e fisiologiche originate da modelli di pensiero rigido.

Questo sistema di "Analisi del Linguaggio Rovesciato" è altresì utilizzabile in altri ambiti professionali non strettamente terapeutici, quando sia necessario e conveniente avere un rapido e chiaro quadro sulla veridicità e completezza delle informazioni ricevute in sede di contrattazioni commerciali, transazioni legali e pratiche investigative in genere. Con il supporto di questa analisi sarà facile verificare l'autenticità delle dichiarazioni ricevute e poter quindi valutare con maggior sicurezza la serietà e affidabilità della controparte con cui si sta trattando. Viene così risparmiato tempo prezioso e si evitano spiacevoli sorprese.

Ode an einen kleinen grünen Kittklumpen, den ich eines Sommermorgens in meiner Achselhöhle fand
(Prostetnik Vogon Jeltz)

Oh zerfrettelter Grunzwanzling,
dein Harngedränge ist für mich
Wie Schnatterfleck auf Bienenstich.
Grupp,
ich beschwöre dich!
Mein punzig Turteldrom.
Und drängel reifig mich 
mit krinklen Bindelwördeln,
denn sonst werd ich  rändern dich 
in deine Gobberwarzen
mit meinem Börgelkranze,
wart's nur ab!

Dieses Poem wurde fälschlicherweise Grunthos, dem Aufgeblasenem, zugeschrieben, dessen Haupt-Oeuvre "Meine Lieblingsgluckser zur Badezeit" sich als Plagiat eines Auszugs  von Lothar Günther Frohweins Zyklus "Abschied" herausstellte.
Das genannte Werk weisst allerdings auch erstaunliche Parallelen zur Sonettensammlung "Die zwölf Monate" des obigen Autors auf.

description:
For my write up as well as other students' write up, please go to docs.google.com
username: cgs.111.trans.race.gender
password: performativity

Thank you!

My name is Hao Yang. I am an international student from China. Our project topic is how we can understand regulation and the presence of gender multiplicity here  thinking about the US. I am going to talk about a different perspective of gender, race and beauty ideals in China, which has never been colonized by the U.S, but has a close relationship in economy and culture. Since the last century, the U.S. and China have done a lot of trade. In addition, many Hollywood movies are imported into China and are very popular. Both trade and movies bring a new beauty standard to China. Women in China want to use whitening make-ups to make them look more like super stars in American movies. 
 Besides that, eyelid surgery in China is also very popular. A number of Chinese women don't have a crease in the middle of eyelids, so eyelid surgery has become a significant part of cosmetic surgery in China. Why does one need an extra fold like two cracks running horizontally across the eyelid? Why is the smooth expanse of eyelid skin not perfect enough? The answer is that the desirable eye, the one extolled in the massive cosmetic industry blitz campaigns, is the Western eye, and the two lines provide the border for eye shadow and other make-up applications. This quote from Judith Halberstam's "Female Masculinity" that one of the group members gave to me.


 "Scheer's rhetorical question as to why "the smooth expanse of eyelid skin" is not acceptable is supposed to ironize the relationship between body politics and market demands. A racially marked face is not only marginalized by a kind of economy of beauty, it is also quite obviously the product of imperialist, sexist, and racist ideologies. The cosmetic production of occidental beauty in this scene of cosmetic intervention, then, certainly ups the ante on racist and imperialist notions of aesthetics, but it also has the possibly unforeseen effects of making race obviously artificial, another fiction of culture.
 Cosmetic surgery can in a contradictory way, both bolster dominant ideologies of beauty and power, and it can undermine completely the fixedness of race, class, and gender by making each one surgically or sartorially reproducible."

In terms of gender multiplicity, these are good evidence that there are multiple gender performance based on race and culture instead of binary gender. By looking for the website of Chanel, the whitening products are only in the Chinese website but not in U.S. website. And eyelid surgery is not attractive to American women. In addition, Chinese women would never do tanning but American women love it so much. So we can see gender multiplicity does exist universally, and gender and race cannot be separated. Gender Performance should be related to race, just like we have those stereotypes for women from different races.   For example, Black women are bigger, more voluptuous, White women are tall, and Asian women are short, thin and delicate.

Halberstam, Judith. Female Masculinity. Durham: Duke UP, 1998. Print.
title: Undermining or Reifying the Fixedness of Race/Gender?

description:
This animation illustrates how bacteria form a biofilm. A biofilm - more commonly know as "slime" - is a surface-attached community of microorganisms. Formation of a biofilm involves a series of bacterial processes, including bacterial signalling and quorum sensing, production of pili and secretion of an extracellular polymer matrix.
This animation was produced for the Centre for Microbial Innovation, at the University of Auckland, New Zealand. See cmi.ac.nz for more information.

description:
Fan music video of the Iron Man Trilogy (or series if I'm including The Avengers). I told myself a long time ago that I would do a live-action intro for this when they make 3 movies. Well obviously, I've changed since then, I've become older and more professional, and I think 2 minutes is better than a 44 second remake of an intro (except you, "The Batman"). So instead of remaking the wheel, I thought I would make my own version of the opening titles. Now I know that people have already made videos for the full intro - but mine includes Avengers and Iron Man 3 (and to be cocky, yes I like mine better).

If they make Iron Man 4 though (and I suppose if I can grab better clips from The Avengers), I won't do it. Even though this was relatively short to make, I had fun with it and I'm proud of the finished product. I'm just hoping I can get a full high quality version of the Avengers EMH theme by Bad City... I may come back and do Amazing Spider-Man when its 3rd movie comes out, but who knows, that's a long time from now.

MTV has today revealed Filipino star Sarah Geronimo as the winner of Best Southeast Asia Act at the 2014 MTV EMA, one of the biggest global music events of the year that celebrates the hottest artists from around the world. The 2014 MTV EMA will broadcast live to MTV channels worldwide from the SSE Hydro in Glasgow on Nov. 9 (Nov. 10 in Manila).

Sarah Geronimo now has the opportunity to be voted into the prestigious Worldwide Act award category, the winner of which will be revealed during the 2014 MTV EMA in Glasgow. Cast your vote at mtvema.com to help Sarah Geronimo advance to the final round of Worldwide Act voting as one of 10 international Worldwide Act nominees.

“Congratulations to Sarah Geronimo on becoming the 2014 MTV EMA Best Southeast Asia Act winner! From her nominations at the MTV EMA last year to this year’s Nickelodeon Kids’ Choice Awards, we knew she was a fast rising Asian star. We will continue to elevate Asian artists at international platforms, grow the awareness and appreciation of Asian music and artists for fans around the world to enjoy,” said Paras Sharma, Vice President of MTV Brand and Digital Media, Viacom International Media Networks Asia.

Voting for the nominations for the Worldwide Act category is open from today and will close at 5:59 p.m. Singapore time on Oct. 29. The final list of 10 Worldwide Act nominees will be revealed via mtvema.com on Oct. 30.

description:
Favorite Grazen took command from the start and cruised to his third straight win and first graded stakes victory under jockey Rafael Bejarano in Saturday's $100,000 Affimred Handicap at Hollywood Park.

The victory completed a hat-trick for Bejarano as well as trainer Mike Mitchell, third all-time behind Hall of Fame members Charlie Whittingham and Bobby Frankel with 781Hollywood Park victories.

Nick Alexander's Grazen — tenth in his career debut last fall at Oak Tree — is perfect in three 2009 starts. He won the NTRA Stakes here in April on California Gold Rush Day and then connected in an allowance race prior to his dominating performance in the Grade III Affirmed.

Bejarano sent Grazen to the lead with Fiddlers Afleet hot on his heels. Grazen pulled away from Fiddlers Afleet turning for home and easily held Misremembered at bay through the stretch to win by 2 ¾ legnths while covering 1 1/16 miles on Cushion Track in 1:41.40.
title: Grazen Notches Third Straight Win In Affirmed

description: Nice to see Pilot management walking the parking lot. Had to let them know about some scammers in the lot that tried to sucker me into the old "Truck Driver X just won the lottery and he's giving you a chance to win money" scam. Only this time it was, "Hey! Did you hear about the tanker and the flatbed that just got into it!? Right back here, hurry up!" The whole time I'm thinking it's one of my drivers I'm expecting to show up here at any moment now. So I followed him and he led me to a few other "drivers" sitting on the ground behind a bobtail, one of which had a nice bankroll cupped in his hand. I said I didn't want any part of their scam and walked away. He followed me about half way back to my truck telling me it wasn't a scam, they're just a bunch of truck drivers telling jokes. Yeah? Well, where's the 2 trucks that just got into it. Seen and heard of it a dozen times or more. At least I was smart initially to walk back to my truck and lock it before I got too far away from it. It seemed like he was just trying to lead me away from my truck. That's when I could tell something wasn't right. Pilot management says it happens every day. They usually hightail it when they see them.
title: **PARKING LOT SCAM** Hook, Line, and Sinker - Pilot Truck Stop - Cayce, SC - 5/17/12

description:
Der Verdacht, dass im syrischen Bürgerkrieg Chemiewaffen zum Einsatz kommen, ist kein neuer. 

euronews, der meistgesehene Nachrichtensender in Europa. 
Abonnieren Sie die täglich neue Auswahl internationaler Nachrichten: http://eurone.ws/ZdYLxf
Euronews gibt es in 12 Sprachen :http://eurone.ws/ZcsZh5

Vermutungen und Anschuldigungen gab es stets, handfeste Beweise jedoch kaum. Im April hatte das belgische Fernsehen von einem mutmaßlichen Gebrauch derartiger Kampfstoffe im Norden Syriens berichtet. 
In jener Reportage erklärte ein Arzt, wie den Betroffenen des vermeintlichen Sarin-Angriffes mittels der Verabreichung von Atropin das Leben gerettet wurde.

Sarin wurde Ende der 1930er Jahre von deutschen Chemikern entwickeln, die ursprünglich ein Insektenvernichtungsmittel herstellen wollten und entdeckten, dass sich der Stoff als Waffe eignete. Zum Einsatz kam die Substanz im Zweiten Weltkrieg aber nicht.

Gesicherte Erkenntnis bestehen darüber, dass das Regime des Saddam Hussein 1988 während des Irakkrieges neben anderen chemischen Waffen auch Sarin zu militärischen Zwecken nutzte.

Sarin ist farb-, geruch-, und geschmackslos. Eine Atemmaske allein reicht nicht, um sich gegen das Nervengift zu schützen. Denn auch über Hautkontakt kann der Stoff in den Körper gelangen. Darüber hinaus ist Sarin wasserlöslich und kann deshalb etwa dem Trinkwasser zugesetzt werden.

Bereits kleine Mengen sind tödlich. Ist der Körper mit Sarin in Berührung gekommen, versagen allmählich seine Funktionen.

Während des Kalten Krieges ließen sowohl die Vereinigten Staaten als auch die Sowjetunion große Mengen des Kampfstoffes herstellen. Die britische Armee untersuchte in den 1950er Jahren die Wirkung des Giftes auf den Menschen, dabei kam 1953 ein Soldat ums Leben, nachdem dieser Sarin ausgesetzt worden war.

Die Vereinten Nationen stufen den Stoff offiziell als Massenvernichtungswaffe ein, 
seit 1993 verbietet die Chemiewaffenkonvention den Einsatz von Sarin. Lediglich Angola, Nordkorea, der Südsudan, Ägypten, Somalia und Syrien haben diese Vereinbarung nicht unterzeichnet.

Bei den Anschlägen in der Tokioter U-Bahn 1995 setzte die Aum-Sekte Sarin ein und tötete 13 Menschen.

Durch die Chemiewaffenkonvention von 1993 wurde die Vernichtung der Sarin-Vorräte der unterzeichnenden Länder geregelt. In Syrien, das die Konvention nicht unterstützt, sollen - so schätzen Beobachter - nach wie vor mehr als 1000 Tonnen chemischer Kampfstoffe lagern, darunter Sarin.

title: Massenvernichtungswaffe Sarin

wars  are going to incite, treason and oppression thrive.

the bias to the occupance is of the cormorant fate, 
nevertheless it seems to be a race/running into mischief. 

like the brazen, foolish midas. 
desired, all he touched 
changes into gold 
but earned the death in starvation.  

unassuaged esurience, 
it burns the xeric thirst in the gorge. 
not a real punishment, 
but the abhorrent torments the culprit 

avarice, the fear of the lack. 
a human defect to excel in redundant things 
of the other people, 
with compulsively exaggerated parsimony, 
or the grotesque, ruthless piling up, 
despite of the benefit. 

and he said to them: 
take heed and beware of covetousness, 
for no man his life consists in abundance. 

and to restrain the excess 
the pain will happen after life, 
when they don't fear nor hope anymore. 

and verily, 
the sky's adorned with lucid fires 
And they are missiles for the evil ones 
And for yon has been prepared the doom in the blazing fire. 

When the fetters are around their necks, and chains, 
thus they shall be dragged through the boiling waters 
And thrusted into the fire. 
When they were casted therein, 
They shall hear it braying; and it shall boil, 
Almost bursting, with the fury of the greed. 
Nothing cool shall they taste, nor get any drink therein, 
only pus and sores, the apt reward! 
in a paralysing slurry.

Item Code:TAN05
Dimensions: 18 x 17 x 8 mm
Weight: 16 Carats (3.16 grams)

Tanzanite is the blue/purple variety of the mineral zoisite which was discovered in the Meralani (Merelani) Hills of Northern Tanzania in 1967, near the city of Arusha.

Tanzanite is noted for its remarkably strong trichroism, appearing alternately sapphire blue, violet, and burgundy depending on crystal orientation. It is a remarkably rare gemstone coming exclusively from one small locality in Tanzania.

Tanzanite is now considered to be the most precious and sought after stone in the world. Unsurpassed in its unique beauty, this powerful gemstone is truly one of a kind in every sense.
title: Unheated Natural Tanzanite Crystal with incredible Vivid Blue Hues

What is Cheetah?
A report all about Cheetah for homework/assignment

The cheetah (Acinonyx jubatus) is a large feline (family Felidae, subfamily Felinae) inhabiting most of Africa and parts of Iran. It is the only extant member of the genus Acinonyx. The cheetah can run faster than any other land animal— as fast as 112 to 120 km/h (70 to 75 mph) in short bursts covering distances up to 500 m (1,600 ft), and has the ability to accelerate from 0 to 100 km/h (62 mph) in three seconds.

description:
The Indian Niagara! Visitors look down from a hill-top ledge / balcony, to witness the water leap over the cliff and form Jog Falls!

Jog Falls' cataracts.

Jog Falls is the second-highest plunge waterfall in India. Located near Sagara, Karnataka, these segmented falls are a major tourist attraction. They are also called Gersoppa Falls, Gersoppa Falls and Jogada Gundi.

"Jog Falls is created by the Sharavathi River falling from a height of 253 m (830 ft), making it the second-highest plunge waterfall in Asia after the Nohkalikai Falls with a height of 335 m (1100 ft) in Meghalaya.

Sharavati, a river which rises at Ambutirtha, near Nonabur, in the Thirthahalli taluk and takes the northwesterly course by Fatte petta, receives the Haridravati on the right below Pattaguppe and the Yenne Hole on the left above Barangi. On arriving at the frontier it bends to the west, precipitates itself down the Falls of Gersoppa, and passes that village (properly Geru-Sappe), which is some 29 kilometres distant, discharging into the sea at Honnavar in North Kanara.

The Sharavati, flowing over a very rocky bed about 250 yards wide, here reaches a tremendous chasm, 290 m (960 ft) deep, and the water comes down in four distinct falls. The Raja Fall pours in one unbroken column sheer to the depth of 830 ft (250 m). Halfway down it is encountered by the Roarer, another fall, which precipitates itself into a vast cup and then rushes violently downwards at an angle of forty-five degrees to meet the Raja. A third fall, the Rocket, shoots downwards in a series of jets; while the fourth, the Rani, moves quietly over the mountain side in a sheet of foam. The Tourism Department has built steps from the viewpoint to the bottom of the hill where the waterfall can be seen at the opposite side. There are approximately 1400 steps built to reach the bottom of the hill."

Source - Wikipedia
